You're correct! The `@UseFilters` decorator can be used at the controller or handler level to specify a custom filter for that particular route or method. This allows you to apply filters selectively and customize error handling per endpoint.

However, in our current setup, we have a global exception filter (`AllExceptionsFilter`) that handles all exceptions uniformly across the application. Using the `@UseFilters` decorator is useful when you need more granular control over error handling for specific routes or methods.

